pysum - A pygtk application for create and verify md5 and other checksum
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

pysum depends on the Python runtime and associated libraries.

Python (>= 2.5) : http://www.python.org
PyGTK (>= 2.8) : http://www.pygtk.org


== To run Source code (without installing) ==

You can find the source code of pysum in /src. To run (without installing), in
a terminal use the following syntax:

$ cd src
$ python pysum.py


== To install ==

If you use debian, ubuntu, or some other similar, please using the .deb package
to install pySum

For more detailed instructions (And generic installation instructions), please
see the INSTALL file


